From (H6544) para'; the hair (as dishevelled) -- locks. see HEBREW (H6544) para'
Feminine of (H6545) pera' (in the sense of beginning); leadership (plural concretely, leaders) -- + avenging, revenge. see HEBREW (H6545) pera'
Of Egyptian derivation; Paroh, a general title of Egyptian kings -- Pharaoh.
Of Egyptian derivation; Paroh- Chophra, an Egyptian king -- Pharaoh-hophra.
Or Parpoh Nkow {par-o' nek-o'}; of Egyptian derivation; Paroh-Nekoh (or -Neko), an Egyptian king:
Probably from (H6544) para' and (H6211) ash; a flea (as the isolated insect) -- flea. see HEBREW (H6544) para' see HEBREW (H6211) ash
The same as (H6550) par'osh; Parosh, the name of our Israelite -- Parosh, Pharosh. see HEBREW (H6550) par'osh
From (H6546) par'ah; chieftaincy; Pirathon, a place in Palestine -- Pirathon. see HEBREW (H6546) par'ah
Or Pirathoniy {pir-aw-tho-nee'}; patrial from (H6552) Pir'athown; a Pirathonite or inhabitant of Pirathon -- Pirathonite. see HEBREW (H6552) Pir'athown
Probably from (H6565) parar in the sense of rushing; rapid; Parpar, a river of Syria -- Pharpar. see HEBREW (H6565) parar

column8: abroad, make a breach, break away, down burst out, come spread abroad, compel, disperse, grow,
column9: A primitive root; to break out (in many applications, direct and indirect, literal and figurative) -- X abroad, (make a) breach, break (away, down, -er, forth, in, up), burst out, come (spread) abroad, compel, disperse, grow, increase, open, press, scatter, urge.

column8: breach, breaking forth in, forth, gap
column9: From (H6555) parats; a break (literally or figuratively) -- breach, breaking forth (in), X forth, gap. see HEBREW (H6555) parats

Patronymically from (H6557) Perets; a Partsite (collectively) or descendants of Perets -- Pharzites. see HEBREW (H6557) Perets
Plural of (H6556) perets; breaks; Peratsim, a mountain in Palestine -- Perazim. see HEBREW (H6556) perets
From (H6556) perets and (H5798) Uzza'; break of Uzza; Perets-Uzza, a place in Palestine -- Perez-uzza. see HEBREW (H6556) perets see HEBREW (H5798) Uzza'

column8: break off, deliver, redeem, rend in pieces, tear in pieces

(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6561) paraq; to discontinue -- break off. see HEBREW (H6561) paraq
From (H6561) paraq; rapine; also a fork (in roads) -- crossway, robbery. see HEBREW (H6561) paraq
From (H6561) paraq; soup (as full of crumbed meat) -- broth. See also (H4832) marpe'. see HEBREW (H6561) paraq see HEBREW (H4832) marpe'

column8: break asunder, cast off, cause to cease, clean, defeat, disannul, disappoint,
column9: A primitive root; to break up (usually figuratively, i.e. To violate, frustrate -- X any ways, break (asunder), cast off, cause to cease, X clean, defeat, disannul, disappoint, dissolve, divide, make of none effect, fail, frustrate, bring (come) to nought, X utterly, make void.

column8: break, chop in pieces, lay open, scatter, spread abroad, forth, selves, out,
column9: A primitive root; to break apart, disperse, etc. -- break, chop in pieces, lay open, scatter, spread (abroad, forth, selves, out), stretch (forth, out).
A primitive root; to separate, literally (to disperse) or figuratively (to specify); also (by implication) to wound -- scatter, declare, distinctly, shew, sting.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6567) parash; to specify -- distinctly. see HEBREW (H6567) parash
From (H6567) parash; excrement (as eliminated) -- dung. see HEBREW (H6567) parash
The same as (H6569) peresh; Peresh, an Israelite -- Peresh. see HEBREW (H6569) peresh

From (H6567) parash; a steed (as stretched out to a vehicle, not single nor for mounting (compare (H5483) cuwc)); also (by implication) a driver (in a chariot), i.e. (collectively) cavalry -- horseman. see HEBREW (H6567) parash see HEBREW (H5483) cuwc
Or pathshegen {path-sheh'-gen}; of foreign origin; a transcript -- copy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6572) parshegen -- copy. see HEBREW (H6572) parshegen

Perhaps by compounding (H6567) parash and (H6504) parad (in the sense of straddling) (compare (H6576) parshez); the crotch (or anus) -- dirt. see HEBREW (H6567) parash see HEBREW (H6504) parad see HEBREW (H6576) parshez
From (H6567) parash; exposition -- declaration, sum. see HEBREW (H6567) parash
A root apparently formed by compounding (H6567) parash and that of (H6518) paraz (compare (H6574) parshdon); to expand -- spread. see HEBREW (H6567) parash see HEBREW (H6574) parshdon
Of Persian origin; Parshandatha, a son of Haman -- Parshandatha.
From an unused root meaning to break forth; rushing; Perath (i.e. Euphrates), a river of the East -- Euphrates.
Of Persian origin; a grandee -- (most) noble, prince.
Probably from an unused root meaning to disintegrate; stupidity (as a result of grossness or of degeneracy) -- extremity.
A primitive root; to spread -- spread.
A primitive root; to tear in pieces -- pull in pieces.
Probably from (H6582) pashach; liberation; Pashchur, the name of four Israelites -- Pashur. see HEBREW (H6582) pashach

column7: to strip off, make a dash, raid
column8: fall upon, flay, invade, make an invasion, pull off, put off, make a road, run upon,
column9: A primitive root; to spread out (i.e. Deploy in hostile array); by analogy, to strip (i.e. Unclothe, plunder, flay, etc.) -- fall upon, flay, invade, make an invasion, pull off, put off, make a road, run upon, rush, set, spoil, spread selves (abroad), strip (off, self).
A primitive root; to stride (from spreading the legs), i.e. Rush upon -- go.

A primitive root (identical with (H6585) pasa' through the idea of expansion); to break away (from just authority), i.e. Trespass, apostatize, quarrel -- offend, rebel, revolt, transgress(-ion, -or). see HEBREW (H6585) pasa'
From (H6585) pasa'; a stride -- step. see HEBREW (H6585) pasa'
From (H6586) pasha'; a revolt (national, moral or religious) -- rebellion, sin, transgression, trespass. see HEBREW (H6586) pasha'
A primitive root; to dispart (the feet or lips), i.e. Become licentious -- open (wide).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6622) pathar; to interpret -- make (interpretations), interpreting. see HEBREW (H6622) pathar
(Aramaic) from (H6590) pshar; an interpretation -- interpretation. see HEBREW (H6590) pshar
Corresponding to (H6591) pshar -- interpretation. see HEBREW (H6591) pshar
From the same as (H6580) pash as in the sense of comminuting; linen (i.e. The thread, as carded) -- flax, linen. see HEBREW (H6580) pash
Feminine of (H6593) pishteh; flax; by implication, a wick -- flax, tow. see HEBREW (H6593) pishteh
From (H6626) pathath; a bit -- meat, morsel, piece. see HEBREW (H6626) pathath
Or pothah (Ezek. 13:19) {po-thaw'}; from an unused root meaning to open; a hole, i.e. Hinge or the female pudenda -- hinge, secret participle
Or pith.om {pith-ome'}; from (H6621) petha'; instantly -- straightway, sudden(-ly). see HEBREW (H6621) petha'
Of Persian origin; a dainty -- portion (provision) of meat.
Of Persian origin; a (judicial) sentence -- decree, sentence.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6599) pithgam; a word, answer, letter or decree -- answer, letter, matter, word. see HEBREW (H6599) pithgam

column7: to be spacious, wide or open
column8: allure, deceive, enlarge, entice, flatter, persuade, silly one
column9: A primitive root; to open, i.e. Be (causatively, make) roomy; usually figuratively (in a mental or moral sense) to be (causatively, make) simple or (in a sinister way) delude -- allure, deceive, enlarge, entice, flatter, persuade, silly (one).
From (H6601) pathah and (H410) 'el; enlarged of God; Pethuel, an Israelite -- Pethuel. see HEBREW (H6601) pathah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or pittuach {pit-too'-akh; passive participle of (H6605) pathach; sculpture (in low or high relief or even intaglio) -- carved (work) (are, en-)grave(-ing, -n). see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
Of foreign origin; Pethor, a place in Mesopotamia -- Pethor.

column8: appear, break forth, draw out, let go free, engrave, loose self, be, be set opening,
column9: A primitive root; to open wide (literally or figuratively); specifically, to loosen, begin, plough, carve -- appear, break forth, draw (out), let go free, (en-)grave(-n), loose (self), (be, be set) open(-ing), put off, ungird, unstop, have vent.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6605) pathach; to open -- open. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach

column8: door, entering in, entrance ry, gate, opening, place
column9: From (H6605) pathach; an opening (literally), i.e. Door (gate) or entrance way -- door, entering (in), entrance (-ry), gate, opening, place. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach; opening (figuratively) i.e. Disclosure -- entrance. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach; something opened, i.e. A drawn sword -- drawn sword. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach; opening (the act) -- open(-ing). see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has opened; Pethachjah, the name of four Israelites -- Pethakiah. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Or pethiy {peh'-thee}; or pthaeiy {peth-aw-ee'}; from (H6601) pathah; silly (i.e. Seducible) -- foolish, simple(-icity, one). see HEBREW (H6601) pathah
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H6601) pathah; open, i.e. (as noun) width -- breadth. see HEBREW (H6601) pathah
Of uncertain derivation; probably a figured mantle for holidays -- stomacher.
From (H6612) pthiy; silliness (i.e. Seducibility) -- simple. see HEBREW (H6612) pthiy

column8: bound, bracelet, lace, line, ribbon, thread, wire
column9: From (H6617) pathal; twine -- bound, bracelet, lace, line, ribband, thread, wire. see HEBREW (H6617) pathal

column8: show self froward, show self unsavoury, wrestle
column9: A primitive root; to twine, i.e. (literally) to struggle or (figuratively) be (morally) tortuous -- (shew self) froward, shew self unsavoury, wrestle.
From (H6617) pathal; tortuous (i.e. Crafty) -- crooked. see HEBREW (H6617) pathal
Of Egyptian derivation; Pithom, a place in Egypt -- Pithom.
From an unused root meaning to twist; an asp (from its contortions) -- adder.

From an unused root meaning to open (the eyes); a wink, i.e. Moment (compare (H6597) pith'owm) (used only (with or without preposition) adverbially, quickly or unexpectedly) -- at an instant, suddenly, X very. see HEBREW (H6597) pith'owm
A primitive root; to open up, i.e. (figuratively) interpret (a dream) -- interpret(-ation, -er).
Or pithron {pith-rone'}; from (H6622) pathar; interpretation (of a dream) -- interpretation. see HEBREW (H6622) pathar
Of Egyptian derivation; Pathros, a part of Egypt -- Pathros.

column7: a tribe, desc. from Mizraim, which inhab. S. Eg
column9: Patrial from (H6624) Pathrowc; a Pathrusite, or inhabitant of Pathros -- Pathrusim. see HEBREW (H6624) Pathrowc
A primitive root; to open, i.e. Break -- participle
From (H3318) yatsa'; issue, i.e. (human) excrement -- that (which) cometh from (out). see HEBREW (H3318) yatsa'
From an unused root meaning to be slender; the lotus tree -- shady tree.

column7: small cattle, sheep and goats, flock
column9: Or tsaown (Psalm 144:13) {tseh-one'}; from an unused root meaning to migrate; a collective name for a flock (of sheep or goats); also figuratively (of men) -- (small) cattle, flock (+ -s), lamb (+ -s), sheep((-cote, -fold, -shearer, -herds)).

column7: a place perhaps in the Shephelah of Judah
column9: From the same as (H6629) tso'n used denominatively; sheep pasture; Zaanan, a place in Palestine -- Zaanan. see HEBREW (H6629) tso'n

column8: that which cometh forth out, offspring
column9: From (H3318) yatsa'; issue, i.e. Produce, children -- that which cometh forth (out), offspring. see HEBREW (H3318) yatsa'
From an unused root meaning to establish; a palanquin or canopy (as a fixture); also a species of lizard (probably as clinging fast) -- covered, litter, tortoise.

column8: assemble, fight, perform, muster, wait upon, war
column9: A primitive root; to mass (an army or servants) -- assemble, fight, perform, muster, wait upon, war.

column7: to be inclined, desire, be pleased
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H6623) pithrown in the figurative sense of summoning one's wishes; to please -- will, would. see HEBREW (H6623) pithrown

column8: appointed time, army, battle, company, host, service, soldiers, waiting upon,
column9: Or (feminine) tsbadah {tseb-aw-aw'}; from (H6633) tsaba'; a mass of persons (or figuratively, things), especially reg. Organized for war (an army); by implication, a campaign, literally or figuratively (specifically, hardship, worship) -- appointed time, (+) army, (+) battle, company, host, service, soldiers, waiting upon, war(-fare). see HEBREW (H6633) tsaba'
Or (more correctly) Tsbiyiym {tseb-ee-yeem'}; or Tsbiyim {tseb-ee-yeem'}; plural of (H6643) tsbiy; gazelles; Tseboim or Tsebijim, a place in Palestine -- Zeboiim, Zeboim. see HEBREW (H6643) tsbiy
Feminine active participle of the same as (H6632) tsab; the canopier (with the article); Tsobebah, an Israelitess -- Zobebah. see HEBREW (H6632) tsab
A primitive root; to amass, i.e. Grow turgid; specifically, to array an army against -- fight swell.
From (H6638) tsabah; turgid -- swell. see HEBREW (H6638) tsabah
(Aramaic) from (H6634) tsba'; properly, will; concretely, an affair (as a matter of determination) -- purpose. see HEBREW (H6634) tsba'
Passive participle of the same as (H6648) tseba'; dyed (in stripes), i.e. The hyena -- speckled. see HEBREW (H6648) tseba'
A primitive root; to grasp, i.e. Hand out -- reach.
From (H6638) tsabah in the sense of prominence; splendor (as conspicuous); also a gazelle (as beautiful) -- beautiful(-ty), glorious, goodly, pleasant, roe(-buck). see HEBREW (H6638) tsabah
For (H6645) Tsibyah; Tsibja, an Israelite -- Zibia. see HEBREW (H6645) Tsibyah
For (H6646) tsbiyah; Tsibjah, an Israelitess -- Zibiah. see HEBREW (H6646) tsbiyah
Feminine of (H6643) tsbiy; a female gazelle -- roe. see HEBREW (H6643) tsbiy
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to that of (H6648) tseba'; to dip -- wet. see HEBREW (H6648) tseba'
From an unused root meaning to dip (into coloring fluid); a dye -- divers, colours.
From the same as (H6648) tseba'; variegated; Tsibon, an Idumaean -- Zibeon. see HEBREW (H6648) tseba'

column7: a place probably at S. end of the Dead Sea
column9: Plural of (H6641) tsabuwa'; hyenas; Tseboim, a place in Palestine -- Zeboim. see HEBREW (H6641) tsabuwa'

column8: gather together, heap up, lay up
column9: A primitive root; to aggregate -- gather (together), heap (up), lay up.
From (H6551) Par'osh; a pile -- heap. see HEBREW (H6551) Par'osh
From an unused root apparently meaning to grip; a lock of stalks -- handful.
Contr. From an unused root meaning to sidle off; a side; figuratively, an adversary -- (be-)side.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6654) tsad; used adverbially (with preposition) at or upon the side of -- against, concerning. see HEBREW (H6654) tsad
(Aramaic) from an unused root corresponding to (H6658) tsadah in the sense of intentness; a (sinister) design -- true. see HEBREW (H6658) tsadah

column7: a place on the N. border of Canaan
column9: From the same as (H6654) tsad; a siding; Tsedad, a place near Palestine -- Zedad. see HEBREW (H6654) tsad
A primitive root; to chase; by implication, to desolate -- destroy, hunt, lie in wait.
From (H6663) tsadaq; just; Tsadok, the name of eight or nine Israelites -- Zadok. see HEBREW (H6663) tsadaq
From (H6658) tsadah; design (compare (H6656) tsda') -- lying in wait. see HEBREW (H6658) tsadah see HEBREW (H6656) tsda'
Plural of (H6654) tsad; sides; Tsiddim (with the article), a place in Palestine -- Ziddim. see HEBREW (H6654) tsad
From (H6663) tsadaq; just -- just, lawful, righteous (man). see HEBREW (H6663) tsadaq

column8: cleanse, clear self, be, do justice be turn to righteousness
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) right (in a moral or forensic sense) -- cleanse, clear self, (be, do) just(-ice, -ify, -ify self), (be turn to) righteous(-ness).

From (H6663) tsadaq; the right (natural, moral or legal); also (abstractly) equity or (figuratively) prosperity -- X even, (X that which is altogether) just(-ice), ((un-))right(-eous) (cause, -ly, - ness). see HEBREW (H6663) tsadaq
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6666) tsdaqah; beneficence -- righteousness. see HEBREW (H6666) tsdaqah

From (H6663) tsadaq; rightness (abstractly), subjectively (rectitude), objectively (justice), morally (virtue) or figuratively (prosperity) -- justice, moderately, right(-eous) (act, -ly,-ness). see HEBREW (H6663) tsadaq
Or Tsidqiyahuw {tsid-kee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H6664) tsedeq and (H3050) Yahh; right of Jah; Tsidkijah, the name of six Israelites -- Zedekiah, Zidkijah. see HEBREW (H6664) tsedeq see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A primitive root; to glitter, i.e. Be golden in color -- X fine.
From (H6668) tsahab; golden in color -- yellow. see HEBREW (H6668) tsahab

column8: bellow, cry aloud out, lift up, neigh, rejoice, make to shine, shout
column9: A prim root; to gleam, i.e. (figuratively) be cheerful; by transf. To sound clear (of various animal or human expressions) -- bellow, cry aloud (out), lift up, neigh, rejoice, make to shine, shout.
A primitive root; to glisten; used only as denominative from (H3323) yitshar, to press out oil -- make oil. see HEBREW (H3323) yitshar
From (H6671) tsahar; a light (i.e. Window): dual double light, i.e. Noon -- midday, noon(-day, -tide), window. see HEBREW (H6671) tsahar
Or tsav {tsawv}; from (H6680) tsavah; an injunction -- commandment, precept. see HEBREW (H6680) tsavah
Or tsov {tso}; from an unused root meaning to issue; soiled (as if excrementitious) -- filthy.

Or tsovah {tso-aw'}: feminine of (H6674) tsow'; excrement; generally, dirt; figuratively, pollution -- dung, filth(-iness). Marg. For (H2716) chere'. see HEBREW (H6674) tsow' see HEBREW (H2716) chere'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6677) tsavva'r -- neck. see HEBREW (H6677) tsavva'r

Or tsavvar (Nehemiah 3:5) {tsav-vawr'}; or tsavvaron (Song of Solomon 4:9) {tsav-vaw-rone'}; or (feminine) tsavva.rah (Micah 2:3) {tsav-vaw-raw'}; intensively from (H6696) tsuwr in the sense of binding; the back of the neck (as that on which burdens are bound) -- neck. see HEBREW (H6696) tsuwr
Or Tsowbah {tso-baw'}; or Tsobah {tso-baw'}; from an unused root meaning to station; a station; Zoba or Zobah, a region of Syria -- Zoba, Zobah.

A primitive root; to lie alongside (i.e. In wait); by implication, to catch an animal (figuratively, men); (denominative from (H6718) tsayid) to victual (for a journey) -- chase, hunt, sore, take (provision). see HEBREW (H6718) tsayid

column7: to lay charge (upon), give charge (to), command, order
column8: appoint, forbid, give a charge, give a, give in, send with commander send a messenger, put, set in order
column9: A primitive root; (intensively) to constitute, enjoin -- appoint, (for-)bid, (give a) charge, (give a, give in, send with) command(-er, -ment), send a messenger, put, (set) in order.
A primitive root; to screech (exultingly) -- shout.
From (H6681) tsavach; a screech (of anguish) -- cry(-ing). see HEBREW (H6681) tsavach
From an unused root meaning to sink: an abyss (of the sea) -- deep.
A primitive root; to cover over (the mouth), i.e. To fast -- X at all, fast.
Or tsom {tsome}; from from (H6684) tsuwm; a fast -- fast(-ing). see HEBREW (H6684) tsuwm

column7: little one, a man of Issachar
column9: From (H6819) tsa'ar; small; Tsuar, an Israelite -- Zuar. see HEBREW (H6819) tsa'ar
A primitive root; to overflow -- (make to over-)flow, swim.
From (H6687) tsuwph; comb of honey (from dripping) -- honeycomb. see HEBREW (H6687) tsuwph

column4: noun masculine; Adjective, of a people
column9: Or Tsowphay {tso-fah'-ee}; or Tsiyph {tseef}; from (H6688) tsuwph; honey-comb; Tsuph or Tsophai or Tsiph, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine -- Zophai, Zuph. see HEBREW (H6688) tsuwph
From an unused root meaning to expand, breadth; Tsophach, an Israelite -- Zophah.
From (H6852) tsaphar; departing; Tsophar, a friend of Job -- Zophar. see HEBREW (H6852) tsaphar
A primitive root; to twinkle, i.e. Glance; by analogy, to blossom (figuratively, flourish) -- bloom, blossom, flourish, shew self.

column7: to constrain, bring into straits, press upon
column8: constrain, distress, lie sore, oppressor, straiten
column9: A primitive root; to compress, i.e. (figuratively) oppress, distress -- constrain, distress, lie sore, (op-)press(-or), straiten.
A primitive root (identical with (H6693) tsuwq through the idea of narrowness (of orifice)); to pour out, i.e. (figuratively) smelt, utter -- be molten, pour. see HEBREW (H6693) tsuwq
Or (feminine) tsuwqah {tsoo-kaw'}; from (H6693) tsuwq; a strait, i.e. (figuratively) distress -- anguish, X troublous. see HEBREW (H6693) tsuwq

column8: adversary, assault, beset, besiege, bind up, cast, distress, fashion,
column9: A primitive root; to cramp, i.e. Confine (in many applications, literally and figuratively, formative or hostile) -- adversary, assault, beset, besiege, bind (up), cast, distress, fashion, fortify, inclose, lay siege, put up in bags.

column8: edge, mighty God one, rock, sharp, stone, strength, strong
column9: Or tsur {tsoor}; from (H6696) tsuwr; properly, a cliff (or sharp rock, as compressed); generally, a rock or boulder; figuratively, a refuge; also an edge (as precipitous) -- edge, X (mighty) God (one), rock, X sharp, stone, X strength, X strong. See also (H1049) Beyth Tsuwr. see HEBREW (H6696) tsuwr see HEBREW (H1049) Beyth Tsuwr

column7: rock, a Midianite, also a Gibeonite
column9: The same as (H6697) tsuwr; rock; Tsur, the name of a Midianite and of an Israelite -- Zur. see HEBREW (H6697) tsuwr
Feminine of (H6697) tsuwr; a rock (Job 28:10); also a form (as if pressed out) -- form, rock. see HEBREW (H6697) tsuwr

column7: my rock is El, a Levite
column9: From (H6697) tsuwr and (H410) 'el; rock of God; Tsuriel, an Israelite -- Zuriel. see HEBREW (H6697) tsuwr see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: my rock is the Almighty, a Simeonite
column9: From (H6697) tsuwr and (H7706) Shadday; rock of (the) Almighty; Tsurishaddai, an Israelite -- Zurishaddai. see HEBREW (H6697) tsuwr see HEBREW (H7706) Shadday
A primitive root; to blaze -- burn.
From (H6705) tsachach; dazzling, i.e. Sunny, bright, (figuratively) evident -- clear, dry, plainly, white. see HEBREW (H6705) tsachach
From an unused root meaning to glow; parched -- dried up.
A primitive root; to glare, i.e. Be dazzling white -- be whiter.
From (H6705) tsachach; glaring, i.e. Exposed to the bright sun -- higher place, top. see HEBREW (H6705) tsachach
Feminine of (H6706) tschiyach; a parched region, i.e. The desert -- dry land. see HEBREW (H6706) tschiyach
From (H6706) tschiyach; bare spot, i.e. In the glaring sun -- higher place. see HEBREW (H6706) tschiyach
From an unused root meaning to putrefy; stench -- ill savour.
From (H6705) tsachach; a dry place, i.e. Desert -- drought. see HEBREW (H6705) tsachach
A primitive root; to laugh outright (in merriment or scorn); by implication, to sport -- laugh, mock, play, make sport.
From (H6711) tsachaq; laughter (in pleasure or derision) -- laugh(-ed to scorn). see HEBREW (H6711) tsachaq
From an unused root meaning to dazzle; sheen, i.e. Whiteness -- white.
From the same as (H6713) tsachar; whiteness; Tsochar, the name of a Hittite and of an Israelite -- Zohar. Compare (H3328) Yitschar. see HEBREW (H6713) tsachar see HEBREW (H3328) Yitschar
From the same as (H6713) tsachar; white -- white. see HEBREW (H6713) tsachar
From (H6680) tsavah; a ship (as a fixture) -- ship. see HEBREW (H6680) tsavah
From the same as (H6678) Tsowba'; station; Tsiba, an Israelite -- Ziba. see HEBREW (H6678) Tsowba'

column8: catch, food, hunter, that which he took in hunting, venison, victuals
column9: From a form of (H6679) tsuwd and meaning the same; the chase; also game (thus taken); (generally) lunch (especially for a journey) -- X catcheth, food, X hunter, (that which he took in) hunting, venison, victuals. see HEBREW (H6679) tsuwd
From the same as (H6718) tsayid; a huntsman -- hunter. see HEBREW (H6718) tsayid
Or tsedah {tsay-daw'}; feminine of (H6718) tsayid; food -- meat, provision, venison, victuals. see HEBREW (H6718) tsayid

column7: a Phoenician city on the Mediterranean coast, also a son of Canaan
column9: Or Tsiydon {tsee-done'}; from (H6679) tsuwd in the sense of catching fish; fishery; Tsidon, the name of a son of Canaan, and of a place in Palestine -- Sidon, Zidon. see HEBREW (H6679) tsuwd
Patrial from (H6721) Tsiydown; a Tsidonian or inhabitant of Tsidon -- Sidonian, of Sidon, Zidonian. see HEBREW (H6721) Tsiydown

column8: barren, drought, dry land, place, solitary place, wilderness
column9: From an unused root meaning to parch; aridity; concretely, a desert -- barren, drought, dry (land, place), solitary place, wilderness.
From the same as (H6723) tsiyah; a desert -- dry place. see HEBREW (H6723) tsiyah
From the same as (H6723) tsiyah in the sense of conspicuousness (compare (H5329) natsach); a monumental or guiding pillar -- sign, title, waymark. see HEBREW (H6723) tsiyah see HEBREW (H5329) natsach

column7: a mountain in Jerusalem, also a name for Jer
column9: The same (regularly) as (H6725) tsiyuwn; Tsijon (as a permanent capital), a mountain of Jerusalem -- Zion. see HEBREW (H6725) tsiyuwn

column7: an overseer of Nethinim, also an Israelite family
column9: Or Tsicha({tsee-khaw'}; as if feminine of (H6704) tsicheh; drought; Tsicha, the name of two Nethinim -- Ziha. see HEBREW (H6704) tsicheh

column7: wild beast of the desert, that dwell in inhabiting the wilderness
column8: wild beast of the desert, that dwell in inhabiting the wilderness
column9: From the same as (H6723) tsiyah; a desert-dweller, i.e. Nomad or wild beast -- wild beast of the desert, that dwell in (inhabiting) the wilderness. see HEBREW (H6723) tsiyah
From an unused root meaning to confine; the pillory -- stocks.
From (H6819) tsa'ar; small; Tsior, a place in Palestine -- Zior. see HEBREW (H6819) tsa'ar

Or tsits {tseets}; from (H6692) tsuwts; properly, glistening, i.e. A burnished plate; also a flower (as bright-colored); a wing (as gleaming in the air) -- blossom, flower, plate, wing. see HEBREW (H6692) tsuwts

column7: a pass between the Dead Sea and Jer
column9: The same as (H6731) tsiyts; bloom; Tsits, a place in Palestine -- Ziz. see HEBREW (H6731) tsiyts
Feminine of (H6731) tsiyts; a flower -- flower. see HEBREW (H6731) tsiyts
Feminine of (H6731) tsiyts; a floral or wing-like projection, i.e. A forelock of hair, a tassel -- fringe, lock. see HEBREW (H6731) tsiyts

column8: ambassador, hinge, messenger, pain, pang, sorrow
column9: From (H6696) tsuwr; a hinge (as pressed in turning); also a throe (as a phys. Or mental pressure); also a herald or errand-doer (as constrained by the principal) -- ambassador, hinge, messenger, pain, pang, sorrow. Compare (H6736) tsiyr. see HEBREW (H6696) tsuwr see HEBREW (H6736) tsiyr
The same as (H6735) tsiyr; a form (of beauty; as if pressed out, i.e. Carved); hence, an (idolatrous) image -- beauty, idol. see HEBREW (H6735) tsiyr
A denominative from (H6735) tsiyr in the sense of ambassador; to make an errand, i.e. Betake oneself -- make as if...had been ambassador. see HEBREW (H6735) tsiyr
From (H6751) tsalal; shade, whether literal or figurative -- defence, shade(-ow). see HEBREW (H6751) tsalal
(Aramaic) probably corresponding to (H6760) tsala' in the sense of bowing; pray -- pray. see HEBREW (H6760) tsala'
A primitive root; to roast -- roast.
Feminine of (H6738) tsel; Tsillah, an antediluvian woman -- Zillah. see HEBREW (H6738) tsel
From (H6749) tsalal in the sense of rolling; a (round or flattened) cake -- cake. see HEBREW (H6749) tsalal

column8: break out, come mightily, go over, be good, be meet, be profitable, cause to, effect,
column9: Or tsaleach {tsaw-lay'-akh}; a primitive root; to push forward, in various senses (literal or figurative, transitive or intransitive) -- break out, come (mightily), go over, be good, be meet, be profitable, (cause to, effect, make to, send) prosper(-ity, -ous, - ously).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6743) tsalach; to advance (transitive or intransitive) -- promote, prosper. see HEBREW (H6743) tsalach
From (H6743) tsalach; something protracted or flattened out, i.e. A platter -- pan. see HEBREW (H6743) tsalach
From (H6743) tsalach; something prolonged or tall, i.e. A vial or salt-cellar -- cruse. see HEBREW (H6743) tsalach
From (H6743) tsalach; something advanced or deep, i.e. A bowl; figuratively, the bosom -- bosom, dish. see HEBREW (H6743) tsalach
Passive participle of (H6740) tsalah; roasted -- roast. see HEBREW (H6740) tsalah
A primitive root; properly, to tumble down, i.e. Settle by a waving motion -- sink. Compare (H6750) tsalal, (H6751) tsalal. see HEBREW (H6750) tsalal see HEBREW (H6751) tsalal

A primitive root (identical with (H6749) tsalal through the idea of vibration); to tinkle, i.e. Rattle together (as the ears in reddening with shame, or the teeth in chattering with fear) -- quiver, tingle. see HEBREW (H6749) tsalal

A primitive root (identical with (H6749) tsalal through the idea of hovering over (compare (H6754) tselem)); to shade, as twilight or an opaque object -- begin to be dark, shadowing. see HEBREW (H6749) tsalal see HEBREW (H6754) tselem
From (H6751) tsalal; shade -- shadow. see HEBREW (H6751) tsalal

column7: give shade, you who turn to me! an Israelite woman
column9: From (H6752) tselel and the active participle of (H6437) panah; shade-facing; Tselelponi, an Israelitess -- Hazelelponi (including the article). see HEBREW (H6752) tselel see HEBREW (H6437) panah
From an unused root meaning to shade; a phantom, i.e. (figuratively) illusion, resemblance; hence, a representative figure, especially an idol -- image, vain shew.
(Aramaic) or tslem (Aramaic) {tsel-em'}; corresponding to (H6754) tselem; an idolatrous figure -- form, image. see HEBREW (H6754) tselem

column4: proper name, of a mountain ; proper name, masculine
column7: a mountain near Shechem, also perhaps a snowcapped mountain of unc. location
column9: From (H6754) tselem; shady; Tsalmon, the name of a place in Palestine and of an Israelite -- Zalmon. see HEBREW (H6754) tselem
From (H6738) tsel and (H4194) maveth; shade of death, i.e. The grave (figuratively, calamity) -- shadow of death. see HEBREW (H6738) tsel see HEBREW (H4194) maveth
Feminine of (H6757) tsalmaveth; shadiness; Tsalmonah, a place in the Desert -- Zalmonah. see HEBREW (H6757) tsalmaveth
From (H6738) tsel and (H4513) mana'; shade has been denied; Tsalmunna, a Midianite -- Zalmunna. see HEBREW (H6738) tsel see HEBREW (H4513) mana'
A primitive root: probably to curve; used only as denominative from (H6763) tsela', to limp (as if one-sided) -- halt. see HEBREW (H6763) tsela'
From (H6760) tsala'; a limping or full (figuratively) -- adversity, halt(-ing). see HEBREW (H6760) tsala'
The same as (H6761) tsela'; Tsela, a place in Palestine -- Zelah. see HEBREW (H6761) tsela'

column8: beam, board, chamber, corner, leaf, plank, rib, side chamber
column9: Or (feminine) tsaltah {tsal-aw'}; from (H6760) tsala'; a rib (as curved), literally (of the body) or figuratively (of a door, i.e. Leaf); hence, a side, literally (of a person) or figuratively (of an object or the sky, i.e. Quarter); architecturally, a (especially floor or ceiling) timber or plank (single or collective, i.e. A flooring) -- beam, board, chamber, corner, leaf, plank, rib, side (chamber). see HEBREW (H6760) tsala'

column7: father of one of the builders of the Jerusalem wall
column9: From an unused root of unknown meaning; Tsalaph, an Israelite -- Zalaph.
From the same as (H6764) Tsalaph and (H259) 'echad; Tselophchad, an Israelite -- Zelophehad. see HEBREW (H6764) Tsalaph see HEBREW (H259) 'echad
From (H6738) tsel and (H6703) tsach; clear shade; Tseltsach, a place in Palestine -- Zelzah. see HEBREW (H6738) tsel see HEBREW (H6703) tsach

From (H6750) tsalal reduplicated; a clatter, i.e. (abstractly) whirring (of wings); (concretely) a cricket; also a harpoon (as rattling), a cymbal (as clanging) -- cymbal, locust, shadowing, spear. see HEBREW (H6750) tsalal
From an unused root meaning to split; fissure; Tselek, an Israelite -- Zelek.
From the feminine of (H6738) tsel; shady; Tsillethai, the name of two Israelites -- Zilthai. see HEBREW (H6738) tsel
A primitive root; to thirst (literally or figuratively) -- (be a-, suffer) thirst(-y).
From (H6770) tsame'; thirsty (literally or figuratively) -- (that) thirst(-eth, -y). see HEBREW (H6770) tsame'
From (H6770) tsame'; thirst (literally or figuratively) -- thirst(-y). see HEBREW (H6770) tsame'
Feminine of (H6772) tsama'; thirst (figuratively, of libidinousnes) -- thirst. see HEBREW (H6772) tsama'
From (H6771) tsame'; a thirsty place, i.e. Desert -- drought, dry ground, thirsty land. see HEBREW (H6771) tsame'
A primitive root; to link, i.e. Gird; figuratively, to serve, (mentally) contrive -- fasten, frame, join (self).

column8: acre, couple, together, two donkeys, yoke of oxen
column9: A yoke or team (i.e. Pair); hence, an acre (i.e. Day's task for a yoke of cattle to plough) -- acre, couple, X together, two (donkeys), yoke (of oxen).
From an unused root meaning to fasten on; a veil -- locks.
From (H6784) tsamaq; a cake of dried grapes -- bunch (cluster) of raisins. see HEBREW (H6784) tsamaq

column8: bear, bring forth, cause to, make to bud forth, make to grow again, cause to spring forth,
column9: A primitive root; to sprout (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative) -- bear, bring forth, (cause to, make to) bud (forth), (cause to, make to) grow (again, up), (cause to) spring (forth, up).

column8: branch, bud, that which where grew upon, springing
column9: From (H6779) tsamach; a sprout (usually concrete), literal or figurative -- branch, bud, that which (where) grew (upon), spring(-ing). see HEBREW (H6779) tsamach
Or tsamid {tsaw-meed'}; from (H6775) tsamad; a bracelet or arm-clasp; generally, a lid -- bracelet, covering. see HEBREW (H6775) tsamad
From the same as (H6777) tsammah; a noose (as fastening); figuratively, destruction -- robber. see HEBREW (H6777) tsammah
Or tsmithuth {tsem-ee-thooth'}; from (H6789) tsamath; excision, i.e. Destruction; used only (adverbially) with prepositional prefix to extinction, i.e. Perpetually -- ever. see HEBREW (H6789) tsamath
A primitive root; to dry up -- dry.
From an unused root probably meaning to be shaggy; wool -- wool(-len).
Patrial from an unused name of a place in Palestine; a Tsemarite or branch of the Canaanites -- Zemarite.

column7: a place in Benjamin, also a mountain in Ephraim
column9: Dual of (H6785) tsemer; double fleece; Tsemarajim, a place in Palestine -- Zemaraim. see HEBREW (H6785) tsemer
From the same as (H6785) tsemer; fleeciness, i.e. Foliage -- highest branch, top. see HEBREW (H6785) tsemer

column7: to put an end to, exterminate
column9: A primitive root; to extirpate (literally or figuratively) -- consume, cut off, destroy, vanish.

column7: a desert area which included Kadesh-barnea
column9: From an unused root meaning to prick; a crag; Tsin, a part of the Desert -- Zin.
From an unused root meaning to be prickly; a thorn; hence, a cactus-hedge -- thorn.

column9: From (H6942) qadash; a sanctum; Kedesh, the name of four places in Palestine -- Kedesh. see HEBREW (H6942) qadash

column8: consecrated thing, dedicated thing, hallowed thing, holiness, most holy day, portion, thing, saint,
column9: From (H6942) qadash; a sacred place or thing; rarely abstract, sanctity -- consecrated (thing), dedicated (thing), hallowed (thing), holiness, (X most) holy (X day, portion, thing), saint, sanctuary. see HEBREW (H6942) qadash
From (H6942) qadash; a (quasi) sacred person, i.e. (technically) a (male) devotee (by prostitution) to licentious idolatry -- sodomite, unclean. see HEBREW (H6942) qadash

column7: sacred, a place in the desert
column9: The same as (H6945) qadesh; sanctuary; Kadesh, a place in the Desert -- Kadesh. Compare (H6947) Qadesh Barnea'. see HEBREW (H6945) qadesh see HEBREW (H6947) Qadesh Barnea'

From the same as (H6946) Qadesh and an otherwise unused word (apparently compounded of a correspondent to (H1251) bar and a derivative of (H5128) nuwa') meaning desert of a fugitive; Kadesh of (the) Wilderness of Wandering; Kadesh-Barnea, a place in the Desert -- Kadesh-barnea. see HEBREW (H6946) Qadesh see HEBREW (H1251) bar see HEBREW (H5128) nuwa'
Feminine of (H6945) qadesh; a female devotee (i.e. Prostitute) -- harlot, whore. see HEBREW (H6945) qadesh

column8: be set on edge, be blunt
column9: A primitive root; to be dull -- be set on edge, be blunt.

column7: to gather as an assembly or congregation
column8: assemble selves together, gather selves together
column9: A primitive root; to convoke -- assemble (selves) (together), gather (selves) (together).
From (H6950) qahal; assemblage (usually concretely) -- assembly, company, congregation, multitude. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal
From (H6950) qahal; an assemblage -- assembly, congregation. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal

column7: a collector (of sentences), "a preacher", a son of David
column9: Feminine of active participle from (H6950) qahal; a (female) assembler (i.e. Lecturer): abstractly, preaching (used as a \"nom de plume\", Koheleth) -- preacher. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal

column7: assembly, a place in the desert
column9: From (H6950) qahal; convocation; Kehelathah, a place in the Desert -- Kehelathah. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal
From an unused root meaning to ally oneself; allied; Kehath, an Israelite -- Kohath.
Patronymically from (H6955) Qhath; a Kohathite (collectively) or descendants of Kehath -- Kohathites. see HEBREW (H6955) Qhath

Or qav {kawv}; from (H6960) qavah (compare (H6961) qaveh); a cord (as connecting), especially for measuring; figuratively, a rule; also a rim, a musical string or accord -- line. Compare (H6978) qav-qav. see HEBREW (H6960) qavah see HEBREW (H6961) qaveh see HEBREW (H6978) qav-qav

column7: spue out, vomit out, up, up again
column8: spue out, vomit out, up, up again
column9: Or qayah (Jer. 25:27) {kaw-yaw'}; a primitive root; to vomit -- spue (out), vomit (out, up, up again).
A form collateral to (H3553) kowba'; a helmet -- helmet. see HEBREW (H3553) kowba'

column8: gather together, look, patiently, tarry, wait for, on, upon
column9: A primitive root; to bind together (perhaps by twisting), i.e. Collect; (figuratively) to expect -- gather (together), look, patiently, tarry, wait (for, on, upon).
From (H6960) qavah; a (measuring) cord (as if for binding) -- line. see HEBREW (H6960) qavah
A primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) detest -- begrieved, loathe self.

column8: aloud, bleating, crackling, cry out, fame, lightness, lowing, noise,
column9: Or qol {kole}; from an unused root meaning to call aloud; a voice or sound -- + aloud, bleating, crackling, cry (+ out), fame, lightness, lowing, noise, + hold peace, (pro-)claim, proclamation, + sing, sound, + spark, thunder(-ing), voice, + yell.
From (H6963) qowl and (H3050) Yahh; voice of Jah; Kolajah, the name of two Israelites -- Kolaiah. see HEBREW (H6963) qowl see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

A primitive root; to rise (in various applications, literal, figurative, intensive and causative) -- abide, accomplish, X be clearer, confirm, continue, decree, X be dim, endure, X enemy, enjoin, get up, make good, help, hold, (help to) lift up (again), make, X but newly, ordain, perform, pitch, raise (up), rear (up), remain, (a-)rise (up) (again, against), rouse up, set (up), (e-)stablish, (make to) stand (up), stir up, strengthen, succeed, (as-, make) sure(-ly), (be) up(-hold, - rising).

column8: appoint, establish, make, raise up self, arise up, make to stand, set up
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H6965) quwm -- appoint, establish, make, raise up self, (a-)rise (up), (make to) stand, set (up). see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
From (H6965) quwm; height -- X along, height, high, stature, tall. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
From (H6965) quwm; elevation, i.e. (adverbially) erectly (figuratively): upright. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm

column7: to chant an elegy or dirge
column9: A primitive root; to strike a musical note, i.e. Chant or wail (at a funeral) -- lament, mourning woman.
Probably from (H6972) quwts in the original sense of cutting off; curtailment; Koa, a region of Bab. -- Koa. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts
Or qoph {kofe}; probably of foreign origin; a monkey -- ape.
A primitive root; to clip off; used only as denominative from (H7019) qayits; to spend the harvest season -- summer. see HEBREW (H7019) qayits

column7: to feel a loathing, abhorrence, or sickening dread
column8: abhor, be distressed, be grieved, loathe, vex, be weary
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H6972) quwts through the idea of severing oneself from (compare (H6962) quwt)); to be (causatively, make) disgusted or anxious -- abhor, be distressed, be grieved, loathe, vex, be weary. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts see HEBREW (H6962) quwt

A primitive root (identical with (H6972) quwts through the idea of abruptness in starting up from sleep (compare (H3364) yaqats)); to awake (literally or figuratively) -- arise, (be) (a-)wake, watch. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts see HEBREW (H3364) yaqats
Or qots {kotse}; from (H6972) quwts (in the sense of pricking); a thorn -- thorn. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts
The same as (H6975) qowts; Kots, the name of two Israelites -- Koz, Hakkoz (including the article). see HEBREW (H6975) qowts
Feminine passive participle of (H6972) quwts in its original sense; a forelock (as shorn) -- lock. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts
From (H6957) qav (in the sense of a fastening); stalwart -- X meted out. see HEBREW (H6957) qav

column8: break down, cast out, destroy, dig
column9: A primitive root; to trench; by implication, to throw forth; also (denominative from (H7023) qiyr) to wall up, whether literal (to build a wall) or figurative (to estop) -- break down, cast out, destroy, dig. see HEBREW (H7023) qiyr
From (H6979) quwr; (only plural) trenches, i.e. A web (as if so formed) -- web. see HEBREW (H6979) quwr
Or Qore (1 Chronicles 26:1) {ko-ray'}; active participle of (H7121) qara'; crier; Kore, the name of two Israelites -- Kore. see HEBREW (H7121) qara'
Or qorah {ko-raw'}; from (H6979) quwr; a rafter (forming trenches as it were); by implication, a roof -- beam, roof. see HEBREW (H6979) quwr
A primitive root; to bend; used only as denominative for (H3369) yaqosh, to set a trap -- lay a snare. see HEBREW (H3369) yaqosh
From the passive participle of (H6983) qowsh and (H3050) Yahh; entrapped of Jah; Kushajah, an Israelite -- Kushaiah. see HEBREW (H6983) qowsh see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H6990) qatat in the sense of abbreviation; a little, i.e. (adverbially) merely -- very. see HEBREW (H6990) qatat
From an unused root meaning to cut off; ruin -- destroying, destruction.
From the same as (H6986) qeteb; extermination -- destruction. see HEBREW (H6986) qeteb
From (H6999) qatar; perfume -- incense. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
Feminine passive participle of (H6999) qatar; perfumed; Keturah, a wife of Abraham -- Keturah. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
A primitive root; to clip off, i.e. (figuratively) destroy -- be cut off.
A primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) put to death -- kill, slay.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6991) qatal; to kill -- slay. see HEBREW (H6991) qatal
From (H6991) qatal; a violent death -- slaughter. see HEBREW (H6991) qatal

column8: be a make small thing, be not worthy
column9: A primitive root (rather denominative from (H6996) qatan); to diminish, i.e. Be (causatively, make) diminutive or (figuratively) of no account -- be a (make) small (thing), be not worthy. see HEBREW (H6996) qatan
From (H6994) qaton; a pettiness, i.e. The little finger -- little finger. see HEBREW (H6994) qaton

column8: least, lesser, little one, smallest, one, quantity, thing, younger,
column9: Or qaton {kaw-tone'}; from (H6962) quwt; abbreviated, i.e. Diminutive, literally (in quantity, size or number) or figuratively (in age or importance) -- least, less(-er), little (one), small(-est, one, quantity, thing), young(-er, -est). see HEBREW (H6962) quwt

column7: the small, father of a postexilic Isr
column9: The same as (H6996) qatan; small; Katan, an Israelite -- Hakkatan (including the article). see HEBREW (H6996) qatan

column8: crop off, cut down up, pluck
column9: A primitive root; to strip off -- crop off, cut down (up), pluck.

column8: burn incense, sacrifice upon, altar for incense, kindle, offer incense, a sacrifice
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H7000) qatar through the idea of fumigation in a close place and perhaps thus driving out the occupants); to smoke, i.e. Turn into fragrance by fire (especially as an act of worship) -- burn (incense, sacrifice) (upon), (altar for) incense, kindle, offer (incense, a sacrifice). see HEBREW (H7000) qatar
